## DO's (Always Follow)

### Code Quality
- ✅ Write complete, production-ready code (no placeholders)
- ✅ Add TypeScript interfaces for ALL props and data
- ✅ Include JSDoc comments for complex functions
- ✅ Use named exports (better tree-shaking)
- ✅ Implement proper error boundaries
- ✅ Add loading states with skeleton screens
- ✅ Write mobile-first responsive code

### Performance
- ✅ Use React Server Components by default
- ✅ Add `'use client'` only when necessary (hooks, state, browser APIs)
- ✅ Lazy load below-the-fold components: `const Component = dynamic(() => import('./Component'))`
- ✅ Optimize images with `<Image priority>` for LCP
- ✅ Debounce search inputs (300ms)
- ✅ Memoize expensive calculations with `useMemo`

### Accessibility
- ✅ Add ARIA labels to interactive elements
- ✅ Ensure keyboard navigation works (focus states)
- ✅ Maintain 4.5:1 contrast ratio (WCAG AA)
- ✅ Use semantic HTML (`<nav>`, `<main>`, `<section>`)
- ✅ Add alt text to all images
- ✅ Test with screen reader in mind

### SEO & Metadata
- ✅ Add proper metadata in `layout.tsx`
- ✅ Use structured data (JSON-LD)
- ✅ Generate sitemap.xml
- ✅ Implement robots.txt
- ✅ Add Open Graph tags
- ✅ Include canonical URLs

