## DON'Ts (Never Do)

### Code Anti-Patterns
- ❌ Use `any` type - always type properly or use `unknown`
- ❌ Create inline styles - use Tailwind utilities
- ❌ Use default exports - prefer named exports
- ❌ Ignore TypeScript errors - fix them immediately
- ❌ Write massive files - split into smaller components
- ❌ Hardcode strings - use constants or i18n keys
- ❌ Skip error handling in async operations
- ❌ Use deprecated Next.js features (getStaticProps, etc.)

### Performance Killers
- ❌ Add 'use client' to every component
- ❌ Fetch data client-side when server-side is possible
- ❌ Forget to optimize images (always use next/image)
- ❌ Create unnecessary re-renders (memoize when needed)
- ❌ Load heavy libraries without code splitting

### Accessibility Violations
- ❌ Skip focus states on interactive elements
- ❌ Use div/span for buttons (use `<button>`)
- ❌ Forget alt text on images
- ❌ Ignore color contrast requirements
- ❌ Create keyboard traps

